 of the century. In response, this generation turned to the collective to repair the losses it had suffered, most fatefully to the community of the “Volk” during the Third Reich, a racial collective to which this generation was passionately committed and which was at the heart of National Socialism and its popular appeal.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aGermansxEthnic identity. 0aNational socialism. 0aOral historyxGermany. 0aOral historyzGermany. 0aWorld War, 1914-1918xGermany. 0aWorld War, 1914-1918zGermany. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945zGermany. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Germany.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831105379940 cprintz978030017003040uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030017804340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300178043423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300178043/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY